      <h2>Rules & Regulations</h2>

      <!-- Club Mania (1st Semester) -->
      <div class="event">
          <h3>General Rules :-</h3>
          <p>
             Eligibility: Open to all students registered for the event.<br>
             Registration: Participants must preregister online and provide accurate details.<br>  
             Timing: The event begins promptly at decided time. Latecomers will not be allowed to participate.<br>
             Participation: This is an individual event; no team entries are permitted.<br>
             Internet Access: Participants must ensure a stable internet connection for the quiz.
          </p>
          <h3>Specific Guidelines :-</h3>
          <p>
             The quiz will be conducted online.<br>
             Each question will have a time limit to ensure fairness.<br>
             Questions will focus on drone technology, realworld applications, and general advancements in technology.<br>
             Participants must be present in the designated, monitored room on the TIT campus.
          </p>
          <h3>Judging Criteria :-</h3>
          <p>
             Each correct answer awards specifc points.<br>
             No negative marking for incorrect answers.<br>
             In case of a tie, a bonus round or sudden-death question will decide the winner.<br>
             Scoring will prioritize correct answers within the time limit.
          </p>
          <h3>Code of Conduct :-</h3>
          <p>
             Participants must maintain a respectful and competitive spirit.<br>
             No external assistance (online searches, notes, or help from peers) is allowed.<br>
             All devices used for the quiz must be muted to avoid distractions.<br>
             Disruptive behavior will lead to immediate removal from the venue.
          </p>
          <h3>Disqualification Condition :-</h3>
          <p>
             Use of unfair means, including but not limited to:<br>
             Searching answers online.<br>
             Communicating with other participants during the quiz.<br>
             Failing to stay within the monitored quiz area.<br>
             Tampering with the quiz platform or any technical misconduct.<br>
             Non-adherence to time limits or refusing to follow instructions from coordinators.
          </p>
          <h3>Safety Measures :-</h3>
          <p>
             Venue Protocols:<br>
             The event will be conducted in a secure and monitored room to ensure fairness.<br>
             Surveillance cameras or invigilators will monitor the venue.<br>
             Health and Safety:<br>
             Participants are advised to maintain decorum and avoid crowding the venue.<br>
             Emergency contacts and coordinators will be available on-site for assistance.
          </p>
          
